#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.65"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.65:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.65:0.2"
msgid "7. Arahantavagga"
msgstr "7. The Perfected Ones"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 65. Abhinandamānasutta → abhinandanasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn22.65:0.3"
msgid "65. Abhinandamānasutta"
msgstr "65. When You Take Pleasure"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.65:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.65:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn22.65:1.3"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena … pe … pahitatto vihareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’"
"ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”"

msgctxt "sn22.65:1.4"
msgid "“Abhinandamāno kho, bhikkhu, baddho mārassa;"
msgstr "“When you take pleasure, mendicant, you’re bound by Māra."

msgctxt "sn22.65:1.5"
msgid "anabhinandamāno mutto pāpimato”ti."
msgstr "Not taking pleasure, you’re free from the Wicked One.”"

msgctxt "sn22.65:1.6"
msgid "“Aññātaṃ, bhagavā, aññātaṃ, sugatā”ti."
msgstr "“Understood, Blessed One! Understood, Holy One!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.76"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.65:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāsī”ti?"
msgstr "“But how do you see the detailed meaning of my brief statement?”"

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.2"
msgid "“Rūpaṃ kho, bhante, abhinandamāno baddho mārassa;"
msgstr "“Sir, when you take pleasure in form you’re bound by Māra."

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.3"
msgid "anabhinandamāno mutto pāpimato."
msgstr "Not taking pleasure, you’re free from the Wicked One."

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.4"
msgid "Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "When you take pleasure in feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.5"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.6"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.7"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ abhinandamāno baddho mārassa;"
msgstr "consciousness you’re bound by Māra."

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.8"
msgid "anabhinandamāno mutto pāpimato."
msgstr "Not taking pleasure, you’re free from the Wicked One."

msgctxt "sn22.65:2.9"
msgid ""
"Imassa khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief "
"statement.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.65:3.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhu."
msgstr "“Good, good, monk!"

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.2"
msgid ""
"Sādhu kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ "
"ājānāsi."
msgstr ""
"It’s good that you understand the detailed meaning of what I’ve said in "
"brief like this."

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.3"
msgid "Rūpaṃ kho, bhikkhu, abhinandamāno baddho mārassa;"
msgstr "When you take pleasure in form you’re bound by Māra."

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.4"
msgid "anabhinandamāno mutto pāpimato."
msgstr "Not taking pleasure, you’re free from the Wicked One."

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.5"
msgid "Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "When you take pleasure in feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.6"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.7"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.8"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ abhinandamāno baddho mārassa;"
msgstr "consciousness you’re bound by Māra."

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.9"
msgid "anabhinandamāno mutto pāpimato."
msgstr "Not taking pleasure, you’re free from the Wicked One."

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.10"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho, bhikkhu, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena attho "
"daṭṭhabbo”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"This is how to understand the detailed meaning of what I said in brief.” …"

msgctxt "sn22.65:3.11"
msgid "aññataro ca pana so bhikkhu arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And that mendicant became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.65:3.12"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
